# Sloboda, Republic of Buryatia

}}
Sloboda () is a rural locality (a selo) in Bichursky District, Republic of Buryatia, Russia. The population was 556 as of 2010. There are 5 streets.
Geography
Sloboda is located 27&nbsp;km east of Bichura (the district's administrative centre) by road. Poselye is the nearest rural locality.
